11. O-O { White needs to get the d2-Knight out of the pin before continuing with the initiative. This also eliminates a dangerous attacker. } Nd7 { Intending to trade off one of White's most dangerous attacking pieces, whilst also developing one of our own pieces. } 
12. Ndf3 { White intends to replace the Knight on e5 with their other Knight. White also threatens Bxh6 now. } Nxe5 { Eliminating one of White's attackers and opening up the way for the c8-Bishop. } 
13. Nxe5 Qf6 
