12. bxc3 O-O { We also complete our development. White's pawn structure is scattered all around. On the other hand, White has the pair of Bishops. This would be a good point to stop in general, but I feel that it might be useful to go a bit deeper as White's next move is more or less forced in my opinion. } 
13. a4 { I think that it is really important for White to strike back and counter-attack this way before Black has time to mop up White's pawns. } a6 ( { The simplest and the most human. } 13...bxa4 { is the other move, which also equalizes all the same. It simply leads to having to know a lot more variations as White has many different ways to continue. Therefore I found } ) ( 13...a6 { simpler. } ) 
