18. Qd2 { White makes a general useful improving move. } Rfe8 $10  { We also make a useful, improving move, not committing anything and making a slight improvement over the Kasimdzhanov-Stevic, 2022 game. White won that game, although Black was okay for most parts of the game. I also feel that Black didn't quite conduct that game in the best way possible, and to do that it is important to understand the potential of Black's Knights.

There are a few different plans for Black, which depend on how White continues. The pressure on c4 can be defended with ...Bd5, which also opens up the e4-square for the f6-Knight. The most obvious destination for the d7-Knight is eventually d3. The a8-Rook can go to d8 to support this Knight's journey. Overall, I think the position is about balanced. } 
