7. f3 { The most straightforward way to defend the e4-pawn, retaining White's center. Although this is necessary from White's perspective in order to keep their center protected, the drawback of this move is that there is no way back for White's e5-Knight. } O-O { We complete our Kingside development for now. Black's threat is to continue with ...c5, breaking White's center.

In general, this a fresh, new direction with limited games. As such it offers an excellent opportunity for us to ambush our opponents with our opening preparation. } 
8. a4 { This is a pretty common and standard strategic operation against Black's present pawn structure with the pawns on b5 and c4. White simply undermines Black's pawns on the Queenside. } c5! { This is the theme in which the concept of this entire variation is based on. Black is in time to exert pressure on White's center to counter White's pressure on the Queenside. This entire operation is time-based in the sense that it works only because Black is able to achieve this strategic operation in time. } 
9. Be3 { The best way to retain White's center. } cxd4 { Breaking White's center, which is what Black set out to do from the beginning. } 
10. Qxd4 { A natural recapture. } Qe7 { A typical idea - to exert pressure on the e5-Knight. Moving the Queen away from d8 to e7 also frees the d8-square for the Rook and prepares ...Rd8, attacking White's Queen, and eventually the e5-Knight. } 
11. axb5 { The only move. White has to weaken the c4-pawn by eliminating the b5-pawn first. } Rd8 { Going after White's Queen, which is the main point of vulnerability in White's position right now. } 
12. Qxc4 { Just in time. Althought Black's Queen has a gun to the e5-Knight's head, the white Queen immediately puts a gun to the b4-Bishop's head as well. } Be6 { Continuing to go after White's Queen, which is still vulnerable. } 
13. Qe2 { The only square for the Queen. But this blocks White's pieces on the Kingside. On the other hand, White is two pawns up. } Qc7 { The point. With the White Queen away from the defence of the c3-Knight, Black sets up a double attack - attacking both of White's Knights at once. } 
14. Nc4 { Pretty much the only way to defend the c3-Knight for now. } Nbd7 {[%mdl 32768]} { Just continuing to develop. Black sets up threats like ...Nc5 and ...Rac8. } 
