14. Qe3 { Pretty much the only way to counter and create a threat against Black. White creates a threat by pinning the Knight on the d-file. } Nd5 $132  ( 14...Nd5 { The simple point. With this discovered attack, Black forces equality. White has to take } 15.Qxd4 Bxg5 16.Nxd5 exd5 17.Bxd5 Bxd5 18.Qxd5 Qxd5 19.Rxd5 { and now Black simply equalizes after } 19...Bf6 { . } 20.Nd7 { is not a problem as after } 20...Bxb2 21.Rb1 Rfe8 { White has to contend with their back rank weakness. With 14...Nd5 Black has equalized comfortably and the game will head towards a draw. } ) 
