17. Bf3 ( { The only move. The natural } 17.Nf6+ { would actually be quite bad for White, as after } 17...Kd8 18.O-O N8d7 { White will be forced to trade their Knight, which is their best asset in this position. } ) N8d7 { Developing our Knight to a natural square and covering the f6-point. } 
18. O-O Nd5 $15  { Taking the Knight to a good square, exerting pressure on c3, and controlling the f4 and f6-squares. Right now Black has things under control. Black is a pawn up and has addressed White's threats sufficiently well. It is on White to show how they want to continue the initiative. } 
