[Event "Queen's Gambit Accepted: Simplified"]
[White "Reference Games"]
[Black "How to Use Reference Games"]
[Date "2025.01.07"]
[Result "*"]
[SourceTitle "https://www.chessable.com/variation/47406956"]

{ Welcome to this reference games chapter! My general didactic approach consists of three different ways of learning:
1) learning by doing;
2) learning by observing others doing;
3) learning by feedback.

Chessable’s MoveTrainer is an example of the 3rd way of learning. This is very valuable, but I don’t believe it’s sufficient by itself. So in this Reference Games Chapter you can learn in the 2nd way, observing how other chess players use this opening. Which pawn structures arise from the Queen's Gambit Accepted, and how strong players navigate them.

My suggestion is that you browse the games in a relatively quick way. This will allow you to absorb various patterns that occur in these games and connect them to other patterns that you already know. And those patterns will eventually improve your intuition when playing this opening, which in turn will help you find good moves. } 1. -- *

