34. Rc1 Nc6 
35. Bc3 g5 
36. Bb5 Ba3 
37. Rc2 Nd4+ {[%csl Rc2,Re2]} { As good as a draw offer, as this forces an endgame with opposite coloured bishops. Having said that, White's pair of bishops was effectively controlling Black's Knight in any case. } 
38. Bxd4 Rxd4 
39. Rc7+ {[%csl Re7,Rh7]} Kf6 
40. Rxh7 { White wins back the pawn and substantiates his claim to equality. } Bb4 {[%cal Gd4d2]} 
41. Bd3 e5 {[%cal Ge5e4][%csl Rd3]} 
42. f3 e4 
