{ I had played my very talented opponent in a tournament that happened prior to this one. It was clear that my opponent had excellent potential. Therefore I decided to be completely solid in this game and offer him no chances to show what he is capable of. :-) } 1. d4 d5 {[%mdl 32768]} 
2. c4 dxc4 { The QGA has been my go-to choice in recent times whenever I want to stay solid. } 
3. Nf3 Nf6 
4. e3 e6 
5. Bxc4 Be7 
6. O-O O-O 
7. Nc3 c5 
8. a3 a6 { Following the Hikaru-Gukesh game from the Candidates, which I remembered. :-) } 
9. dxc5 { My opponent attempts to go into a slightly more pleasant endgame. } Qxd1 { I didn't really want to give him the chance to get a game. } 
10. Rxd1 Bxc5 { The endgame is pretty equal. } 
11. b4 {[%csl Rc5]} Be7 
12. Be2 b5 {[%cal Gc8b7]} 
13. Nd2 {[%cal Gd2b3]} Bb7 
14. Nb3 {[%cal Gb3a5][%csl Rb7]} Nc6 {[%csl Ga5]} { I have completed my development. Now it's time to trade everything off. } 
15. Bb2 Rfd8 
16. f3 Rxd1+ 
17. Rxd1 Rd8 
18. Rxd8+ { An easy draw, as I intended. My opponent was significantly lower-rated than me during this game, but gained about a 100 points in the next rating list. } 1/2-1/2

