24. Qb7 {[%csl Ra8,Rd7]} Rd8 
25. Bg5 {[%csl Rd7,Rd8]} { Black seems to be in potential danger. But how dangerous is it really? } Qb8 
26. Qd5 ( 26.Rb1 Qxb7 27.Rxb7 f6 $10 { is just equal. } ) Qb6+ { Using this counter-play, Black neutralizes White's threats. } 
27. Be3 Qb2+ 
28. Kg3 Qb5 { Black has solved all the problems. } 
29. Rd1 Qxd5 
30. Rxd5 Kf8 
31. Bxa7 Ke8 { The position is completely equal and heading towards a draw. } 
32. Rg5 {[%csl Rg7]} Ra8 
33. Be3 Ra6 {[%cal Ga6g6]} { Professional and clinical. } 
34. Rxg7 Rg6+ 
35. Rxg6 hxg6 { An opposite colour Bishop endgame. This is just a draw. } 
36. Kf4 Bb5 
37. Kg3 Bd7 
38. Kf4 Bb5 
39. Kg3 Bd7 { A solid and seamless draw from Anish. Not giving White even an inch. } 
1/2-1/2

